      'result': """CVE-2025-34036 is an OS command injection vulnerability found in white-labeled Digital Video Recorders (DVRs) manufactured by TVT. This flaw specifically impacts a custom HTTP service known as "Cross Web Server," which operates on TCP ports 81 and 82.

The vulnerability arises because the web interface of the affected DVRs fails to properly sanitize input within the URI path during the language extraction functionality. When the server processes a request to `/language/[lang]/index.html`, it uses the `[lang]` input directly and unsafely in a `tar` extraction command without adequate escaping. This critical oversight enables an unauthenticated remote attacker to inject arbitrary shell commands, ultimately achieving root-level command execution on the affected device.

Exploitation evidence of this vulnerability was observed by the Shadowserver Foundation on February 6, 2025, UTC. While the vulnerability affects TVT DVRs, Red Hat Product Security has confirmed that this CVE does not impact any currently supported Red Hat products. Security researchers have also created resources, such as GitHub repositories, to simulate this vulnerability safely and develop Nuclei templates for testing its presence."""
